<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618193>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A, Habitus of Grebennikovius basilewskyi (Balthasar, 1960) new combination, paratype male; B, habitus of Epactoides humberti (Paulian, 1975), holotype; C, anterolateral view of elytra of G. basilewskyi showing the carina on the elytral edge. Scale bar = 1 mm for Figs. A, B; Fig. C not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618193/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618195>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Aedeagus in dorsal (A), right lateral (B) and left lateral (C, D) view. A–C, Grebennikovius basilewskyi (Balthasar, 1960) new combination; D, Epactoides humberti (Paulian, 1975). Scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618195/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618197>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Map showing the location of the Uluguru Mountains (black) in Tanzania. Light grey indicates mountains and dark grey indicates the great lakes (modified from Mlambo et al. 2014)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618197/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

